  "prompt": "What are the best hotels to stay at in San Francisco?",
  "response": "San Francisco is home to some of the best hotels that offer luxury, convenience, and unique experiences. Here are some highly-rated options:\n\n1. **Fairmont San Francisco**: Known for its historic charm and luxury, the Fairmont offers stunning views of the city and the Bay. The service and amenities are top-notch, including a health club, spa, and several dining options.\n\n2. **The Ritz-Carlton, San Francisco**: Located in Nob Hill, this hotel provides exceptional service, elegant rooms, and fine dining. It also has a spa and fitness center for guests.\n\n3. **Four Seasons Hotel San Francisco**: Situated near Market Street, this hotel is renowned for its sophisticated design, excellent service, and amenities such as a full-service spa, pool, and fitness center.\n\n4. **Hotel Nikko San Francisco**: Offering a blend of contemporary elegance and high-end comfort, Hotel Nikko is conveniently located near Union Square. It features modern rooms, a pool, a fitness center, and live music at its nightclub.\n\n5. **W San Francisco**: This trendy hotel in the SoMa district provides stylish accommodations and a vibrant nightlife scene. Guests can enjoy the fitness center, spa services, and upscale dining options.\n\n6. **The St. Regis San Francisco**: Known for its luxurious ambiance and attentive service, The St. Regis provides spacious rooms, a world-class spa, and gourmet dining.\n\n7. **Palace Hotel, a Luxury Collection Hotel**: This historic hotel combines classic elegance with modern amenities. It's located near the Financial District and offers a beautiful indoor pool, impressive architecture, and fine dining.\n\n8. **Hotel Drisco Pacific Heights**: For those looking for a more intimate and luxurious boutique experience, Hotel Drisco offers well-appointed rooms, excellent service, and complimentary breakfast, afternoon wine receptions, and evening chauffeur service.\n\n9. **InterContinental San Francisco**: This contemporary hotel near Moscone Center is ideal for business travelers and tourists alike, offering spacious rooms, a full-service spa, and top-tier dining options.\n\n10. **Park Central San Francisco**: Ideally located near major attractions such as Chinatown and Union Square, this hotel offers stylish rooms, excellent views, and a fitness center.\n\nEach of these hotels has its own unique features and advantages, so the best choice depends on your personal preferences and the purpose of your visit to San Francisco.",
